Updates Zenefits when your application is ready to begin working for a company

Updates Zenefits when your application is ready to begin working for a company  You use your installation's custom data to store data that may differ for different people subscriptions but be the same for all their flows. For example, an expense management application might use this to set the person's specific policy and their expense approval options.  In addition to updating the fields values through this endpoint, this custom data can be read through the through the Person Subscriptions fields values. It can also be read and written in your custom Module UI.
Trigger collection of new information from a person outside of the standard flows

Updates Zenefits when your application is ready to begin working for a company  You use your installation's custom data to store data that may differ for different company installations but be the same for all subscriptions and flows . For example, an expense management application might use this to set the company's specific policy type and the list of all the policy options it offers for all that company's employees.  In addition to updating the fields values through this endpoint, this custom data can be read through the through the Company Installations fields values. It can also be read and written in your custom Module UI.
Returns information about the subscriptions for people in the company where your integration was added

executor_description: Returns information about a person's T&A hours

queryParams.description: Person that this time duration is logged for
Activity type. Will be one of the following  work meal_break

Will be one of the following, depending on how the duration was added or edited   effective: Default state overridden: Overridden by approver. A new time_duration object (with state 'effective') will be created with the overriding details deleted: Deleted correction: Added as a correction in an already past pay period deleted_correction`: Deleted as a correction in an already past pay period

Will be one of the following, based on the time data itself  valid: Default state exceeds_maximum: Exceeds maximum of 24 hours overlapping_same_day: Overlapping with another time duration overlapping_previous_day: Overlapping with previous day overlapping_next_day: Overlapping with next day missing_clock_out: Missing clock out missing_clock_in: Missing clock in
Number of hours logged
ISO 8601 date. Non-nullable. Which timesheet date this duration applies to

ISO 8601 datetime. When this time duration started. Null for certain reporting types (e.g. self reporting hours). If non-null, hours will be the difference between start and end.  Note the date component of start may not match date if is_overnight is set below, e.g. if someone works Friday from 1AM to 3AM but that should be counted against Thursday's sheet for total hours/overtime/etc

ISO 8601 datetime. When this time duration ended. Null for certain reporting types (e.g. self reporting hours). If non-null, hours will be the difference between start and end.  Note the date component of end may not match date if is_overnight is set below
Whether this time duration has been marked as part of an overnight shift
Whether this time duration has been approved
ISO 8601 datetime. When this time duration was approved. Null if unapproved.
Person who approved this time duration. Null if unapproved OR if auto approved by the system.
A dictionary of Labor Group Type ID keys to Labor Group ID values
